  <refnamediv>
    <refname>bwborder</refname>
    <refpurpose>Find border for an image</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   outm = bwborder(inm, conn)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>inm :</term>
      <listitem><para> Source Image (must be in binary)</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>conn :</term>
      <listitem><para> 4 or 8 neighbourhood</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>outm :</term>
      <listitem><para> Output image (in double)</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
Extracts contours from binary images, by detecting which pixel valued 1 has
at least one neighbor valued 0. conn is 4 or 8 dependig if the detection is to
be made in 4 or 8-neighborhood. The final border is 8-connected if
4-neighbors are used, and 4-connected if 8-neighbors are used.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
inm = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/big_sq.png"));
outm = bwborder(im2bw(inm,0.5), 4);
imshow(outm);

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

